ResolvedServicePartition.CompareVersion Method

Definition

Namespace:
System.Fabric
Assembly:
System.Fabric.dll

In this Article

Compares two resolved service partitions and identifies which is newer. 

public int CompareVersion (System.Fabric.ResolvedServicePartition other);
Parameters
other
ResolvedServicePartition

The other resolved service partition to compare.

Returns
Int32

Returns Int32.

Exceptions
FabricException

The two ResolvedServicePartition objects are from different service partitions. This can happen if the service is deleted and re-created with the same name and partitioning between two resolve calls.

Remarks

The method takes in a resolved service partition (RSP) argument with the parameter to enable the user to identify which RSP is more up-to-date. A returned value of 0 indicates that the two RSPs have the same version. 1 indicates that the other RSP has an older version. -1 indicates that the other RSP has a newer version.
